==Old English==
===Alternative spellings===
*[[geogoþ|ġeogoþ]]

===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*juwunþ-'', from a Germanic base corresponding to ''[[geong|ġeong]]'' + ''[[-þ]]''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''[[juguð]]'' (Dutch ''[[jeugd]]''), Old High German ''[[jugund]]'' (German ''[[Jugend]]'').

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈjeoɣʊθ/}}

===Noun===
'''ġeoguþ''' {{f}} (''genitive'' '''[[geoguþe|ġeoguþe]]''')

# (period of) [[youth]], [[childhood]]
# young people, young warriors, [[youth]]

===Descendants===
*English: [[youth]]

